@node Intro

There were so much converters using either @{I}alien libraries@{IU} or just called a @{I}Shell command@{UI} to execute a script. Most of them didn't manage correctly the memory. I decided to write PCD Manager.

PCD Manager is a thumbnail builder with @{B}built-in selection@{UB} for converting to IFF 24 or IFF 8. It has been written in @{B}C non-ANSI@{UB} and @{B}Amiga system friendly@{UB}, to have the @{B}smallest/fastest@{UB} executable file. Compiled with SAS/C 6.58

@{JCENTER}PCD Manager combines all these properties
@{JLEFT}
@{LINDENT 5}
It has a graphical interface on which you can zoom.
It recognizes all the PCD resolutions.
It uses Amiga library routines in a friendly way for speed.
It uses C2P Hardware when found.
It uses an adaptive @{"memory" link Mem} management system.
It doesn't have any Enforcer hits.
It is small.
It doesn't need more stack.
It doesn't @{"need" link Require} any Alien Library.
It takes care for PAL/NTSC.
It saves Index files.
It rotates pictures.
It doesn't need any FPU

@{B}Version 4@{UB}

CyberGFX !
Thumnail is no more limited by CHIP memory.
FotoFun compatible.
No more manual rotation !
Locale used when available.



@{JRIGHT}
Since 4.09, PCD Manager is @{"EMAILWare" link Share}.




@endnode

@node Mem



The free memory amount has a drastic effect on the execution speed. PCD Manager already runs with 2Mb RAM, but to be able to convert the biggest picture in color, it will need 3x6Mb free. PCD uses three several for doing its job in Conversion-Saving-Rotation depending the memory it can allocate.


@endnode


@node Require

@{LINDENT 5}
PCD Manager requires the KickStart 3.0 and the reqtools.library (© Nico François) to be installed. A Shell version, can be found in the directory names 'ShellOnly'. This needs only the Kick 2.04 and is EMailWare. A PPC version is already ready ! An Arexx AdPro loader which is included, uses this shell version.

Fast Memory welcome: gives more speed!

A ChunkyToPlanar Hardware will be used if recognized.

The middle mouse bouton is recognized.

The program uses extra @{"memory" link Mem} if available, to speed-up its execution time.

An arithmetic coprocessor is not required.

It has been succesfully tested with VMM 2.1 on a A4040.
@{PAR}

@{JCENTER}
Tested on 

A1200+6Mb
A4030+10Mb
A4040+2Mb CHIP !
A4040+22Mb 
A4040+24Mb Kick 3.1 + Retina
A4040+36Mb Kick 3.0/3.1 + Cybervision
SX32 Kick 3.1 + Akiko


@endnode

