@node Prefs


No more tooltypes are used. A new gadget (Prefs) replaces them.

You can now change preferences when the program is running (screen resolution).

"Warning ! The amount of MAX_NB_DIA has an effect on the Chip Memory used. If not enough graphic mem is available, PCD Manager will gradually decrease the number of displayed pictures until it can open the screen." No no... that's old story. NO MORE LIMITATIONS NOW !!!

The prefs file is located in the same directory as PCD Manager. No more ENVARC: needed.

@endnode


@node cmds

@{B}RESOLUTION@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
from 192x256 upto 3072x2048. So, all PCD-resolutions.
@{PARD}
@{B}TRANSFORMATION@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
Here you can select the way PCD handle the colors
@{LINDENT 8}
B&W			Black & white
Normal			Hemm...normal :)
Enhanced		better quality
@{LINDENT 5}
_The Enhanced color mode doesn't use more memory, but the quality is better.

_In BW mode, you only need 1/3 of memory amount required for the color mode.
@{PARD}
@{B}READ@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
Read the given input directory and look for PCD files.
@{PARD}
@{B}START@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
After selecting one or more pictures, handle them and write the resulting IFF24 to the given output directory. PCD Manager adds in commentary the name of the PCD file the picture comes from.
@{PARD}
@{B}ALL, INVERT, CLEAR@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
Quick (de)selecting the pictures.
@{PARD}
@{B}SAVE INDEX@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
Save the thumbnail pictures.
@{B}(Version 4)@{UB} The index format is PRIVATE.
@{PARD}
@{B}LOAD INDEX@{UB}
@{LINDENT 5}
Load an index file. 
@{PARD}
@{B}(Version 4)@{UB} Now you can save to Fotofun: in a friendly way. PCD Manager opens a requester between each pictures so you can change the printing paper.


The @{"Mouse" link mouse} can be used to do more things.




@endnode

@node mouse

PCD pictures are mostly available in several resolutions. Besides the possiblity to use the mouse 
to (de)select pictures, there are some extra:


@{U}Magnifying@{UU}
@{LINDENT 5}
Placing the pointer over a picture in the thumbnail screen, holding right mouse button enable you to magnify it.
@{PARD}
@{U}Rotation@{UU}
@{LINDENT 5}
@{B}(Version 4)@{UB} PCD Manager recognize if a picture is rotated or not.

@{B}(Version 4)@{UB} If you save on a FotoFun: device, it will be handled. Rotation will be ignored.


@endnode

@node KStart


@{LINDENT 10}
Insert a PhotoCD in your favorite CD-Rom player.
Run PCD
Choose the input directory (CD0:....)
Choose the output directory
READ and wait....
SELECT your lovely pictures with the mouse.
Select the resolution and the way PCD tranforms the colors (mouse).
START and wait....
QUIT PCD



@endnode


